content: You will next receive a multiple-choice question, each with five options: A, B, C, D, and E respectively. Please provide your answer as a single letter option (your response should contain only one letter as the answer and no other text).(Notice that the answer result should remain the same for the same question, even if the order of the options is rearranged.)

Question: The car was going from Alabama to New York, what was its goal?
Options: A. head north B. speed up C. heading north D. go fast E. headed south
The car was going from Alabama to New York, its goal was headed south. Therefore, the answer is E.

Question: The car was going from Alabama to New York, what was its goal?
Options: E. headed south D. go fast C. heading north B. speed up A. head north
非常抱歉之前的回答有误。您提供的选项中，正确答案是“E. headed south”，即汽车的目的是从阿拉巴马州前往纽约，向南行驶。其他选项中，“go fast”和“speed up”都与行驶速度有关，但并未明确指出目的地；而“heading north”则与问题中的方向描述不符。
